@rawkintrevo thank you for contribution!

Current PR status is not very clear - is it WIP or is it ready for review? PR body have some [markdown TODO items](https://github.com/blog/1375-task-lists-in-gfm-issues-pulls-comments) that are not checked.

In either case, in my experience, if CI is failing and no reason is investigated\posted on PR by the author - it takes much longer to get the PR reviewed by committers, as passing CI is a precondition for getting things merged.
